President Donald Trump announced that Pastor Andrew Brunson, who was detained in Turkey, is being released and will be returning to the United States. Trump stated that there was no deal made for Brunson's release and that he spoke to Turkey to secure his release. When asked about the situation with Saudi Arabia and the disappearance of journalist Jamal Khashoggi, Trump stated that they are still trying to find out what happened and that it is a serious situation. He mentioned that he plans to speak with King Salman of Saudi Arabia soon. Trump also commented on the relationship between his son-in-law Jared Kushner and Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, stating that it was not any closer than other relationships with countries. Finally, Trump mentioned that the Treasury Secretary's attendance at an investment conference in Saudi Arabia is being evaluated.